<italic>P</italic> value</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Age (years)</td><td>52.9&#x02009;&#x000b1;&#x02009;10.0</td><td>50.9&#x02009;&#x000b1;&#x02009;9.4</td><td char="." align="char">0.412</td></tr><tr><td>Sex (male/female)</td><td>18(53)/16(47)</td><td>21(62)/13(38)</td><td char="." align="char">0.462</td></tr><tr><td>Cervical trauma/cervical spondylosis</td><td>15(44)/19(56)</td><td>18(53)/16(47)</td><td char="." align="char">0.467</td></tr><tr><td>ASA status (I, II or III)</td><td>10(29)/22(65)/2(6)</td><td>14(41)/17(50)/3(9)</td><td char="." align="char">0.958</td></tr><tr><td>Mallampatti grade (1, 2, 3 or 4)</td><td>9(26)/16(47)/8(24)/1(3)</td><td>8(24)/18(53)/6(18)/2(6)</td><td char="." align="char">0.947</td></tr><tr><td>BMI (kg&#x02009;&#x000b7;&#x02009;m<sup>&#x02212;2</sup>)</td><td>25.5&#x02009;&#x000b1;&#x02009;3.9</td><td>25.3&#x02009;&#x000b1;&#x02009;3.3</td><td char="." align="char">0.864</td></tr><tr><td>Mouth opening (cm)</td><td>4.7&#x02009;&#x000b1;&#x02009;0.7</td><td>4.6&#x02009;&#x000b1;&#x02009;0.9</td><td char="." align="char">0.928</td></tr></tbody></table><table-wrap-foot><p>Data are presented as mean&#x02009;&#x000b1;&#x02009;standard deviation or number (proportion, %)</p><p>
